      "comment": "BUMPER SERVICE (5) could be close to a win after placing in two of his last three starts. Both of those were from this barrier, the latest at Charlton last week. Major player. RED KERMIT (6) was a big improver when runner-up last start at Shepparton, beaten 3.5m. Draws wider but should be fitter again third-up and his best results have come at this longer distance. HEAVENS WISH (9) made an impressive start to her career when she led to score by 8m at Ballarat. The second line draw presents more of a challenge but she has upside so could go on with it with even luck. I AM HARRO (10) was racing consistently with a string of top-four finishes before racing wide without cover last start. Freshened since but was kept up to the mark with a trial placing.",
